HEADWORD: Soboles
<hw>Sob"o*les</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a short.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A shoot running along under ground,
forming new plants at short distances.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A sucker,
as of tree or shrub.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soboliferous</ent>⟦br⟧
